9 An Act relating to agriculture; requiring persons
entering certain areas to maintain position of the
10 gate at use; prescribing penalties for violation;
providing for promulgation of rules; providing for
11 codification; and providing an effective date.
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2-34 of Title 2, unless there is
16 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17 A. Any individual entering through gates used for ingress or
18 egress to a property designated as an easement shall maintain the
19 position of the gate upon use.
20 B. 1. Any individual who violates the provisions of subsection
21 A of this section shall, upon conviction, be guilty of a misdemeanor
22 punishable by a fine not more than Five Hundred Dollars ($500.00),
23 by imprisonment in a county jail for not more than ninety (90) days,
24 or by both such fine and imprisonment.
Req. No. 2032 Page 1

1 2. Any individual convicted of a second offense shall, upon
2 conviction, be guilty of a misdemeanor punishable by a fine not more
3 than One Thousand Dollars ($1,000.00), by imprisonment in a county
4 jail for not more than one hundred eighty (180) days, or by both
5 such fine and imprisonment.
6 3. Any individual convicted of a third or subsequent offense
7 shall, upon conviction, be punished by a fine not more than One
8 Thousand Five Hundred Dollars ($1,500.00), by imprisonment in a
9 county jail for not more than one (1) year, or by both such fine and
10 imprisonment.
11 4. Any individual convicted pursuant to the provisions of this
12 subsection shall also be liable for damages.
13 C. The Oklahoma Department of Agriculture, Food, and Forestry
14 shall promulgate rules necessary to implement the provisions of this
15 act.
16 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
